div.small: The Mission of the Kennett School District #39 is to create and maintain a school climate that ensures ALL students will be able to reach their potential academically in order to become productive members of society. We believe that one size does not fit all; as a result, our instruction must be geared to provide the specific needs of each student. We will work diligently toward meeting the state and federal standards while challenging all students in the process. We commit to a comprehensive system of support to assure this outcome.

Kennett School District does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, sex, disability, or age in its programs and activities and provides equal access to the Boy Scouts and other designated youth groups. Read our Non-Discrimination Policy.
Kennett Public Schools | 510 College Ave., Kennett, MO 63857 | Phone 573-717-1100 | Fax 573-717-1016
